Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of N-[(4-Bromo-3,5-difluorine)phenyl]acrylamide in Benzene, Methanol, Pyridine, Ethanol, Acetonitrile, and Toluene at Temperatures between (284.65 and 348.95) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of N-[(4-bromo-3,5-difluorine)phenyl]acrylamide (BDPA) in pure benzene, methanol, pyridine, ethanol, acetonitrile, and toluene was measured at temperatures ranging from (284.65 to 348.95) K under atmospheric pressure. A laser monitoring observation technique was used to determine the dissolution of the solid phase in solid + liquid mixture. The experimental solubility data were correlated with the modified Apelblat equation.
